The two men were arrested with corpses and body parts already stashed in their sacks along the Alamole area by men of Odua Peopleâ€™s Congress and Yoruba Revolutionary Movement.
According to The Daily Trust, a witness said that the suspects have been handed over to the police for further investigation and prosecution.
The state police command is yet to comment on their arrest.
